CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper January 18, 1947, pg. 17, reads: "Students Pay Tribute - Students of Duquesne University paid tribute to Dr. George Washington Carver last week. Program participants include, left to right, seated: Mrs. James C. Campbell and Mrs. W. C. Eichendaw. Standing: Edith Payne, Floyd Rollins, Anna Gray, the Rev. James Dandridge, speaker; Father O'Brien, Mrs. Wingertes, Harriet Coursau and Eleanora Davis. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: George Washing Carver program participants and Duquesne University students, seated from left: Mrs. James C. Campbell, Mrs. W. C. Eichendaw; standing: Edith Payne, Floyd Rollins, Anna Gray, Rev. James Dandridge, Father O'Brien, Mrs. Wingertes, Harriet Coursau, and Eleanora Davis
